verses.verse: To the <S%H5329>chief<s%> <S%H5329>Musician<s%> on <S%H5058>Neginoth,<s%> A <S%H4210>Psalm<s%> or <S%H7892>Song.<s%> <S%H430>God<s%> be <S%H2603>merciful<s%> to us, and <S%H1288>bless<s%> us; and cause his <S%H6440>face<s%> to <S%H215>shine<s%> on us; <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
That your <S%H1870>way<s%> may be <S%H3045>known<s%> on <S%H776>earth,<s%> your <S%H3444>saving<s%> <S%H3444>health<s%> among <S%H3605>all<s%> <S%H1471>nations.<s%>
Let the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> you, O <S%H430>God;<s%> let <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> you.

O let the <S%H3816>nations<s%> be <S%H8056>glad<s%> and <S%H7442>sing<s%> for joy: for you shall <S%H8199>judge<s%> the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H4334>righteously,<s%> and <S%H5148>govern<s%> the <S%H3816>nations<s%> on <S%H776>earth.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
Let the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> you, O <S%H430>God;<s%> let <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H5971>people<s%> <S%H3034>praise<s%> you.
Then shall the <S%H776>earth<s%> <S%H5414>yield<s%> her <S%H2981>increase;<s%> and <S%H430>God,<s%> even our own <S%H430>God,<s%> shall <S%H1288>bless<s%> us.
<S%H430>God<s%> shall <S%H1288>bless<s%> us; and <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H657>ends<s%> of the <S%H776>earth<s%> shall <S%H3372>fear<s%> him.
